<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12117h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12117h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12117h"> 117(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ cambutta (crook)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Et se souvenant de son disciple Gall qu&apos;il avait si s&eacute;v&egrave;rement trait&eacute;, il pria ses moines de lui porter son b&acirc;ton pastoral, sa cambutta, comme une preuve authentique qu&apos;il le relevait de la suspense. <br><font color="green">[And remembering his disciple Gall whom he had so harshly treated, he asked his monks to carry his pastoral crook, his <i>cambutta</i>, as authentic proof that he freed him from the suspension.]</font> <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 172</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
